data_findings.finding: Baseline greedy approach: Place trees one-by-one, starting far away and moving toward center until collision, then back up. Uses weighted random angles (sin(2*angle)) to favor diagonal placements for better corner packing. Uses Shapely for collision detection with STRtree spatial indexing.
